The [[Transport Layer Security]] (TLS) protocol provides the ability to secure communications across networks. This '''comparison of TLS implementations''' compares several of the most notable [[software library|libraries]]. There are several TLS implementations which are [[free software]] and [[Open-source software|open source]].

All comparison categories use the stable version of each implementation listed in the overview section. The comparison is limited to features that directly relate to the TLS protocol.

