ull) | 1948–52 | monthly | Official [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|LDS]] periodical in [[Brazil]] | Brazilian Mission | [[São Paulo]], [[Brazil]] | In [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]].<ref name="Harold B. Lee Library 2010">Harold B. Lee Library, Brigham Young University, Catalog. Accessed 23 July 2010.</ref> |- | ''Liahona'' (Portuguese) | 1953–77 | monthly magazine | Official [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|LDS]] publication in Brazil | Brazilian Mission | [[São Paulo]], [[Brazil]] | In [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]. Replaced ''A Gaivota.''<ref name="Harold B. Lee Library 2010"/> |- | ''Liahona'' (Spanish) | 1955–77 | monthly magazine | Official [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|LDS]] Spanish-language magazine | [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|LDS Church]] | Mexico City, [[Mexico]] | Replaced and unified various Spanish-language periodicals. Published in Mexico City until unified with the other international magazines.<ref>Brigham Young University's Harold B. Lee Library Catalog, accessed 24 March 2010.</ref> |- | ''[[Liahona (magazine)|Liahona]]'' | 1977–current | annual-monthly magazine | Official [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|LDS]] international magazine | [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|LDS Church]] | [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]] | Replaced and unified various older periodicals, all retitled ''Liahona'' as of 1999. Available in 51 languages.<ref>{{cite news | author=Rappleye, Christine | title=Liahona: Same magazine, 51 languages | date=May 6, 2009 | work=[[MormonTimes]] | publisher=[[Deseret News]] | url=http://www.mormontimes.com/around_church/worldwide_church/?id=7627 | accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref> |- | ''Horizon: tijdschrift over de mormoonse gemeenschap''<br>(Horizon: magazine about the Mormon community) | 1982–83 | bi-monthly magazine | independent | | | In [[Dutch language|Dutch]]. Apparently published by local Church members in the Nether