{{Infobox museum | name = Los Palacios Municipal Museum | native_name = Museo Municipal de Los Palacios | native_name_lang = Spanish | image = | imagesize = | caption = | coordinates = | established = {{Start date|1980|12|30|df=y}} | location = [[Los Palacios, Cuba|Los Palacios]], [[Cuba]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Los Palacios Municipal Museum''' is a [[museum]] located in the 21st street [[Los Palacios, Cuba|Los Palacios]], [[Cuba]]. In this building lived [[Enrique Troncoso]], a Cuban revolutionary. It was established as a museum on 30 December 1980.<ref>[http://www.cnpc.cult.cu/institucion/392 Museo Municipal de Los Palacios]</ref>
The museum holds several collections on history, numismatics, local publications and weapons.
