The '''striped marlin''' (''Kajikia audax'') is a species of [[marlin]] found in tropical to temperate [[Indo-Pacific]] oceans not far from the surface. It is a desirable commercial and [[game fish]] with a record weight (in 1982) of {{convert|190|kg|lb|abbr=on}} and a maximum length of {{convert|4.2|m|ft|1|abbr=on}}. The striped marlin' is a predator that hunts during the day in the top 100 m or so of the water column, often near the surface. One of their chief prey is sardines.
== Sustainable consumption == In 2010, Greenpeace International has added the striped marlin to its seafood red list. <!--"The Greenpeace International seafood red list is a list of fish that are commonly sold in supermarkets around the world, and which have a very high risk of being sourced from unsustainable fisheries." --><ref>[http://www.greenpeace.org/international/seafood/red-list-of-species Greenpeace International Seafood Red list]</ref>
